        <div id='wikititle'>
          <div class='pagegroup'><a href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki'>PmWiki</a> /</div>
          <h1 class='pagetitle'>Page specific variables</h1></div>
<!--PageText-->
<div id='wikitext'>
<p>
<a name='trailstart' id='trailstart'></a> 
</p><div style='clear:right; float:right; font-size:smaller; background-color:#eee;' >
<p><span class='wikitrail'>&larr; <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/ConditionalMarkup'>Conditional markup</a> | <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/DocumentationIndex#trailstart' title="trailstart#trailend">Documentation Index</a> | <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageTextVariables'>Page text variables</a> &rarr;</span> 
</p></div>
<div style='clear:right; float:right; font-size:smaller; background-color:#ddd;' >
<p><span class='wikitrail'>&larr; <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/BasicVariables'>Basic Variables</a> | <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/Variables'>Variables</a> | <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageTextVariables'>Page TextVariables</a> &rarr;</span> 
</p></div>
<div style='clear:right;' ><span class='frame rfloat' style='font-size: smaller; background-color: #ffffcc; clear: right;'>authors (intermediate) </span>
</div>
<p class='vspace'><a name='desc' id='desc'></a>This page describes the &ldquo;variables&rdquo; that are associated with pages.  Page variables have the form <code>{$<em>variable</em>}</code>, and can be used in page markup or in certain formatting strings in PmWiki.  For example, the markup &ldquo;<code class='escaped'>{$Group}</code>&rdquo; renders in this page as &ldquo;PmWiki&rdquo;.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>Note: Do not confuse these variables (set and used only in PmWiki pages) with <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/Variables'>PHP variables</a>.  Page variables can be read in PHP with the <a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Cookbook/Functions#PageVar' rel='nofollow'>PageVar()</a> function.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>Note that these variables do not necessarily exist in the PHP code, because they have to be determined for a specific page.  (However, they are usable in <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/FmtPageName'>FmtPageName</a> strings.)
</p>
<p class='vspace'>There is also the form <code>{<em>pagename</em>$<em>variable</em>}</code>, which returns the value of the variable for another page.  For example, &ldquo;<code class='escaped'>{MarkupMasterIndex$Title}</code>&rdquo; displays as &ldquo;Markup Master Index&rdquo;.
</p>
<p class='vspace'><a name='specialreferences' id='specialreferences'></a>
</p><h2>Special references</h2>
<p>Special referenced variables are used to specify the context of the <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/Variables'>variable</a> when:
</p><ul><li>the variable is <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/IncludeOtherPages'>included</a> into a destination (target) page
</li><li>the variable is used in a sidebar, header, or footer
</li></ul><p class='vspace'>Prefixing the variable name with an asterisk (*) means the variable&rsquo;s value is related to the target page or main (body) page.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><ul><li><code>{<strong><code class='escaped'>*$</code></strong>PageVariablename}</code> - prefixed by an asterisk (*) - value reflects target page context
</li></ul><p>Without the asterisk the variable&rsquo;s value is that in the page from which it originates, eg source page of include, sidebar, or header or footer.
</p><ul><li><code>{<strong><code class='escaped'>$</code></strong>PageVariablename}</code> -  retains value in source page context
</li></ul><div class='outdent'>See also <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/BasicVariables#EnableRelativePageVars'><code class='varlink'>&#036;EnableRelativePageVars</code></a>.
</div><div class='outdent'>Special references are also used in <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageTextVariables#specialreferences'>page text variables</a> and <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageListTemplates#specialreferences'>page list templates</a>.
</div><p class='vspace'>For example you can test to see if the page is part of another page
</p><table class='markup vert' align='center'>
      <tr><td class='markup1' valign='top'><pre>(:if ! name {$FullName}:) 
%comment% name of this page is not the same as the page this text was sourced from
-&gt;[[{$FullName}#anchor | more ...]]
(:ifend:)
</pre></td></tr><tr><td 
        class='markup2' valign='top'></td></tr></table>
<p>or refer to the main page in a sidebar, footer, or header
</p><table class='markup horiz' align='center'>
      <tr><td class='markup1' valign='top'><pre>This page is [[{*$FullName}]]
</pre></td><td 
        class='markup2' valign='top'><p>This page is <b class='selflink'>PmWiki.PageVariables</b>
</p>
</td></tr></table>
<p class='vspace'><a name='specialreferencesend' id='specialreferencesend'></a>
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h2>Default page variables</h2>
<p>The page variables defined for PmWiki are:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Action}</code> - page&rsquo;s url action argument, as in &ldquo;browse&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$BaseName}</code> - page&rsquo;s &ldquo;base&rdquo; form (stripping any prefixes or suffixes defined via <code><a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/BasicVariables#BaseNamePatterns'><code class='varlink'>&#036;BaseNamePatterns</code></a></code>) as in &ldquo;PmWiki.PageVariables&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$DefaultGroup}</code> - default group name, as in &ldquo;ÉquipeCalin&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$DefaultName}</code> - name of default page, as in &ldquo;HomePage&rdquo; (take note also of <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/BasicVariables#PagePathFmt'><code class='varlink'>&#036;PagePathFmt</code></a> for setting a homepage for a group)
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Description}</code> - page&rsquo;s description from the <code class='escaped'>(:description:)</code> markup, as in &ldquo;Documentation for &ldquo;variables&rdquo; that are associated with pages.&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$FullName}</code> - page&rsquo;s full name, as in &ldquo;PmWiki.PageVariables&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Group}</code> - page&rsquo;s group name, as in &ldquo;PmWiki&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Groupspaced}</code> - spaced group name, as in &ldquo;PmWiki&rdquo;
<div class='vspace'></div></div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$LastModified}</code> - date page was edited, as in &ldquo;June 29, 2016, at 01:51 PM EST&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$LastModifiedBy}</code> - page&rsquo;s last editor, as in &ldquo;Petko&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$LastModifiedHost}</code> - IP of page&rsquo;s last editor, as in &ldquo;&thinsp;&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$LastModifiedSummary}</code> - Summary from last edit, as in &ldquo;{$WikiTitle, $}SiteAdminGroup&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$LastModifiedTime}</code> - time page was edited in unix-style timestamp, as in &ldquo;1467201112&rdquo;
<div class='indent'>This can be used (preceded by &lsquo;@&rsquo;) in <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/MarkupExpressions#ftime'><code class='escaped'>{(ftime)}</code></a> and other date/time markups.
</div><div class='vspace'></div></div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Name}</code> - page name, as in &ldquo;PageVariables&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Namespaced}</code> - spaced page name, as in &ldquo;Page Variables&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$PageUrl}</code> - page&rsquo;s url, as in &ldquo;<a class='urllink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageVariables' rel='nofollow'>https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageVariables</a>&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$PasswdRead}</code> - &ldquo;read&rdquo; permissions for the page e.g. &ldquo;(protected)&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$PasswdEdit}</code> - &ldquo;edit&rdquo; permissions for the page e.g. &ldquo;(protected)&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$PasswdAttr}</code> - &ldquo;attr&rdquo; permissions for the page e.g. &ldquo;(protected)&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$RequestedPage}</code> - page requested in URL, used on <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/Site/PageNotFound'>Site.PageNotFound</a>. e.g. &ldquo;PmWiki/PageVariables&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$SiteGroup}</code> - default interface group name for e.g. SideBar, forms, templates, as in &ldquo;Site&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$SiteAdminGroup}</code> - default administrative group name for e.g. AuthUser, Blocklist, as in &ldquo;SiteAdmin&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$WikiTitle}</code> - title of the website, as in &ldquo;Wiki temporaire Équipe Calin&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Title}</code> - page title (may differ from Name), as in &ldquo;Page specific variables&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Titlespaced}</code> - either the page title (if defined), or the spaced page name, as in &ldquo;Page specific variables&rdquo;
</div><p class='vspace'>In addition to the above, there are some page-invariant variables available through this markup:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Author}</code> - the name of the person currently interacting with the site, as in &ldquo;&thinsp;&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$AuthId}</code> - current authenticated id, as in &ldquo;&thinsp;&rdquo; <span  style='color: red;'>note the lower case &lsquo;d&rsquo;.</span>
<div class='vspace'></div></div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$Version}</code> - PmWiki version, as in &ldquo;pmwiki-2.2.107&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$VersionNum}</code> - The internal version number, as in &ldquo;2002107&rdquo;
</div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>{$ScriptUrl}</code> - The url to the pmwiki script, as in &ldquo;<a class='urllink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php' rel='nofollow'>https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php</a>&rdquo;
</div><p class='vspace'><a name='security' id='security'></a>
</p><h2>Page variable security ($authpage)</h2>
<p>The form <code>{<em>pagename</em>$<em>variable</em>}</code> or some <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageLists'>PageLists</a>, can display the values for other pages, regardless of the password protections. 
</p>
<p class='vspace'>If the other pages are protected and the visitor has no read permissions, PageVariables, unlike <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageTextVariables'>PageTextVariables</a>, normally display the values. While most variables do not contain sensitive information, some of them could do: {$Title, $}Description and those starting with &#36;LastModified.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>Administrators and module developers can redefine the sensitive page variables to respect authentications, by using the &ldquo;{$authpage" variable instead of "$}page&rdquo; in the definition. The following snippet can be added in local/config.php &mdash; it will rewrite the default possibly sensitive definitions to the secure ones.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><pre class='escaped'>
foreach($FmtPV as $k=&gt;$v) {
  if(preg_match('/^\\$(Title(spaced)?|LastModified(By|Host|Summary|Time)?|Description)$/', $k))
    $FmtPV[$k] = str_replace('$page', '$authpage', $v);
}
</pre>
<p class='vspace'><a name='custompv' id='custompv'></a>
</p><h2>Custom page variables</h2>
<p>You may add custom page variables as a local customization. In a local configuration file or a recipe script, use the variable <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/OtherVariables#FmtPV'><code class='varlink'>&#036;FmtPV</code></a>:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><div class='indent'><pre class='escaped'>
$FmtPV['$VarName'] = "'variable definition'";
$FmtPV['$CurrentSkin'] = '$GLOBALS["Skin"]';
$FmtPV['$WikiTitle'] = '$GLOBALS["WikiTitle"]';
</pre>
</div><p class='vspace'>Defines new Page Variable of name &#36;CurrentSkin, which can be used in the page with <code class='escaped'>{$CurrentSkin}</code> (also for <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/ConditionalMarkup'>Conditional markup</a>).  It&rsquo;s necessary to use the single quotes nested inside double-quotes as shown above (preferred) or a double-quoted string nested inside single-quotes like <em><code class='escaped'>'"this"'</code></em>.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><div class='frame' > 
<p>Please note that the values of the elements of <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/OtherVariables#FmtPV'><code class='varlink'>&#036;FmtPV</code></a> are <code>eval()</code>ed so always sanitize any user input. The following is very insecure:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><div class='indent'><code class='escaped'>$FmtPV['$Var'] = $_REQUEST['Var'];</code> <span  style='color: red;'># critically insecure, allows PHP code injection</span><br /><code class='escaped'>$FmtPV['$Var'] = '"'. addslashes($_REQUEST['Var']).'"';</code> <span  style='color: red;'># critically insecure, allows PHP code injection</span>
</div><p class='vspace'>See the recipe <a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Cookbook/HttpVariables' rel='nofollow'>Cookbook:HttpVariables</a> for a better way to use these variables.
</p></div>
<div class='vspace'></div><h2>See also</h2>
<ul><li><a class='urllink' href='http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Cookbook/More%20custom%20page%20variables' rel='nofollow'>Cookbook:More custom page variables</a>
</li><li><a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/Variables'>PmWiki.Variables</a> &mdash; about variables internal to PmWiki.
</li><li><a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/MarkupMasterIndex'>PmWiki.MarkupMasterIndex</a> &mdash; complete list of PmWiki markups.
</li><li><a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/PageTextVariables'>PageTextVariables</a> &mdash; page variables automatically made available through natural page markup or explicit page markup within the wiki text of the page.
</li><li><a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/MarkupExpressions'>PmWiki.Markup Expressions</a> &mdash; markup expressions can manipulate page variables
</li></ul><div class='vspace'></div><div class='faq' > <a name='faq' id='faq'></a> 
<p class='vspace question'>QIs there a variable like &#36;LastModified, but which shows me the creation time?</p>
<p>No, but you can create one in config.php. For instance:
</p><div class='indent'><pre class='escaped'># add page variable {$PageCreationDate} in format yyyy-mm-dd
$FmtPV['$PageCreationDate'] = 'strftime("%Y-%m-%d", $page["ctime"])';</pre>
</div><p class='vspace'>If you like the same format that you define in config.php with <a class='varlink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/BasicVariables#TimeFmt'><code class='varlink'>&#036;TimeFmt</code></a> use
</p><pre class='escaped'> $FmtPV['$Created'] = "strftime(\$GLOBALS['TimeFmt'], \$page['ctime'])";
</pre>
<p class='vspace question'>Q How can I test if a variable is set and/or not empty?</p>
<p> Use <code> (:if ! equal "{$Variable}" "":) $Variable is not empty. (:ifend:)</code>. Note that undefined/inexistent variables appear as empty ones.
</p>
